    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Schwarber** (77.03) and **Trea Turner** (75.86) as our clear offensive anchors against Imanaga. Both benefit from a favorable wind-out projection and premium lineup spots, with **Trea Turner** specifically maintaining his elite status despite the tempered expectation of a stolen base opportunity against a defensive-minded catcher. While **Junior Caminero** faces a significantly tougher assignment against the sharp arm of Burns (2.76 xERA), his position at the top of the order keeps him in starting territory, though the negative park factors and pitching skill gap limit his ceiling relative to our primary OF duo.\n\nOur middle-infield depth provided the most interesting tactical choices today, with **Caleb Durbin** (65.24) proving to be a high-value play against Gil; his score is buoyed significantly by the favorable matchup against a high-xERA starter (5.74). Conversely, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains the most difficult sit on our bench (42.58). While his raw tools are electric, the combination of a difficult matchup against Luzardo and a bottom-of-the-order assignment suppresses his daily efficiency score below our active threshold. We are also monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (58.97) closely; while he is a strong play, the 42% rain risk introduces a layer of volatility that could threaten his plate appearance volume if the game faces a delay.\n\nAs we manage our limited game caps, we continue to keep **Christian Yelich** on the IL, while **Colt Keith** and **Zac Veen** remain excluded from active consideration due to their roster status. We are maintaining a watchful eye on our depth options like **Lars Nootbaar**, **Luke Raley**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, and **Luis Pena**, though none currently grade out higher than the starters we have locked into the lineup for this afternoon. We expect **Gary Sanchez** and **Dillon Dingler** to provide steady, if unspectacular, production from the catcher slots, provided they continue to avoid the platoon pitfalls present in today's pitching matchups.",
